4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO CONSULTATION BETWEEN
5 STATE AGENCIES AND TRIBAL GOVERNMENTS; REQUIRING STATE AGENCIES TO CREATE WRITTEN
6 CONSULTATION POLICIES; REQUIRING STATE AGENCIES TO DESIGNATE AN EMPLOYEE AS A
7 TRIBAL LIAISON; REVISING AGENCY REPORTING REQUIREMENTS TO THE GOVERNOR; DEFINING
8 "CONSULTATION"; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 2-15-141 AND 2-15-143, MCA.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 2-15-141, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "2-15-141. Definitions. As used in 2-15-141 through 2-15-143, the following definitions apply:
14 (1) "Consultation" means a formal, direct, interactive, and timely process of engagement carried
15 out by state agencies to seek, discuss, and consider the views of tribal governments and, when feasible, to
16 seek agreement regarding state proposed actions that may affect tribal interests.
17 (1) (2) "State agency" means a department, board, or commission of the executive branch of state
18 government.
19 (2) (3) "Tribal government" means the officially recognized government of any tribe or nation.
20 (3) (4) "Tribal officials" means the elected or appointed officials of a tribal government.
21 (4) (5) "Tribe" means an Indian tribe that is recognized by federal law or formally acknowledged by the
22 state."
23
24 Section 2. Section 2-15-143, MCA, is amended to read:
25 "2-15-143. Training and consultation Consultation and training -- duties of tribal liaison. (1)
26 When establishing a government-to-government relationship with tribal governments, a state agency shall:
27 (a) collaborate with tribal governments in the development of policies, agreements, administrative
28 rules, and program implementation that directly affect Indian tribes;
