1 of state agencies and tribal officials, including tribal presiding officers, to discuss:
2 (a) tribal concerns with rules and policies that directly impact tribal government and tribal
3 populations;
4 (b) other issues of concern to either the state or the tribes; and
5 (c) potential solutions to the concerns.
6 (3) (6) By August 15 of each year, each state agency shall submit to the governor its current written
7 consultation policy pursuant to this section, documentation of any relevant trainings completed by its tribal
8 liaison or other agency employees, and a report for the prior fiscal year describing the activities of the state
9 agency relating to tribal government and tribal populations. The report must include:
10 (a) any rule or policy changes that the state agency adopted because of discussions under
11 subsection (2)(a) (5)(a);
12 (b) the process that the state agency has established to identify the activities of the state agency
13 that affect tribes;
14 (c) the efforts of the state agency to promote communication and the government-to-government
15 relationship between the state agency and the tribes; and
16 (d) the efforts of the state agency to ensure tribal consultation and the use of American Indian data
17 in the development and implementation of agency programs that directly affect tribes.
18 (4) (7) By September 15 of each year, the governor shall provide to each tribal government a report
19 with an overview of all state and tribal activities for the prior fiscal year, including a description of the training
20 required under subsection (1) (4). It is the intent of the legislature that this report be prepared within existing
21 levels of funding."
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Notification to tribal governments. The secretary of state shall send a
24 copy of [this act] to each federally recognized tribal government in Montana.
